{"lemma":"خُفْيَةٌ","slug":"خُفْيَةٌ","root":"خ.ف.#","root_slug":"خ-ف-_","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ف-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خُفْيَة","root":"خفي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","adv","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11151"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8F%D9%81%D9%92%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"secret"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of cloak"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَفيَ (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"secret"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"in secrecy, secretly, privately","examples":[{"text":"ٱدْعُوا۟ رَبَّكُمْ تَضَرُّعًا وَخُفْيَةً","english":"Call upon your Lord humbly and secretly."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of خَفِيّ (ḵafiyy)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of خَفيَ.\n\nAdverbial accusative of خُفْيَة (ḵufya, “secret”).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/xuf.ja/","/xuf.ja.tan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11151","headword_ar":"خَفِيَّةٌ","root":"xfY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a deep well;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because its water is not perceived, or not apparent: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well of ancient times, that has become filled up and then dug again:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any well that has been dug and then left until it has become filled up, then dug again, and cleared out:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S:) [opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiYo'N","text_ar":"بَدِىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] accord. to A'Obeyd, it is so called because it is made to appear: (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafaAyaA","text_ar":"خَفَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafiy~aAtN","text_ar":"خَفِيَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK, TA) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tangled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"luxuriant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dense, thicket,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the lion takes as his covert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafiy~ap","text_ar":"خَفِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of a certain place frequented by lions; (S, IB;) and is properly imperfectly decl., so that you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usuwdu xafiy~apa","text_ar":"اُسُودُ خَفِيَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but it may be perfectly decl. in poetry. (IB.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slight taint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"infection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a touch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stroke, of insanity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi xafiy~apN","text_ar":"بِهِ خَفِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In him is a slight taint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of insanity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Menádhir, S, K. *)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","JK","ISk"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}